1 1 test dataset

1.1 1.1 Data normalisation

set.seed(1)

# a collection of stably phosphorylated sites
data(SPSs)
# divides the phospho.L6.ratio data into groups by phosphosites
L6.sites <- gsub(" ", "", sapply(strsplit(rownames(phospho.L6.ratio), "~"), 
                                 function(x){paste(toupper(x[2]), x[3], "", sep=";")}))
phospho.L6.ratio.sites <- t(sapply(split(data.frame(phospho.L6.ratio), L6.sites), colMeans))

# construct design matrix by condition
grps <-  gsub("_.+", "", colnames(phospho.L6.ratio.sites))
f <- grps
design <- model.matrix(~ f - 1)

# phosphoproteomics data normalisation using RUVIII
ctl <- which(rownames(phospho.L6.ratio.sites) %in% SPSs)
phospho.L6.ratio.RUV <- RUVphospho(phospho.L6.ratio.sites, M=design, k=3, ctl=ctl)

cs <- rainbow(length(unique(grps)))
colorCodes <- sapply(f, switch, AICAR=cs[1], Ins=cs[2], AICARIns=cs[3])

# plot before and after RUV clustering
par(mfrow=c(2,2))
plotQC(phospho.L6.ratio.sites, panel = 2, cols=colorCodes, main="Before RUV clustering")
plotQC(phospho.L6.ratio.RUV, panel = 2, cols=colorCodes, main="After RUV clustering")
plotQC(phospho.L6.ratio.sites, cols=colorCodes, labels = colnames(phospho.L6.ratio.sites), panel=4, ylim=c(-20, 20), xlim=c(-30, 30))
plotQC(phospho.L6.ratio.RUV, cols=colorCodes, labels = colnames(phospho.L6.ratio.sites), panel=4, ylim=c(-20, 20), xlim=c(-30, 30))

3 2 Differential phosphorylation anlysis on phospho.L6.ratio.RUV

3.1 2.1 Differential phosphorylation anlysis before normalization

library(limma)
f <- gsub("_exp\\d", "", colnames(phospho.L6.ratio.sites))
X <- model.matrix(~ f - 1)
# fit linear model for each phosphosite
fit <- lmFit(phospho.L6.ratio.sites, X)

# extract top-ranked phosphosites from above linear model fit.
table.AICAR <- topTable(eBayes(fit), number=Inf, coef = 1)
table.Ins <- topTable(eBayes(fit), number=Inf, coef = 3)
table.AICARIns <- topTable(eBayes(fit), number=Inf, coef = 2)

# extract all differentially phosphorylated sites 
DE1.sites <- c(sum(table.AICAR[,"adj.P.Val"] < 0.05), sum(table.Ins[,"adj.P.Val"] < 0.05), sum(table.AICARIns[,"adj.P.Val"] < 0.05))
# defining group comparisons
contrast.matrix1 <- makeContrasts(fAICARIns-fIns, levels=X)  
contrast.matrix2 <- makeContrasts(fAICARIns-fAICAR, levels=X)
fit1 <- contrasts.fit(fit, contrast.matrix1)
fit2 <- contrasts.fit(fit, contrast.matrix2)
table.AICARInsVSIns <- topTable(eBayes(fit1), number=Inf)
table.AICARInsVSAICAR <- topTable(eBayes(fit2), number=Inf)

DE2.sites <- c(sum(table.AICARInsVSIns[,"adj.P.Val"] < 0.05), sum(table.AICARInsVSAICAR[,"adj.P.Val"] < 0.05))

4 3 1-dimentional pathway analysis

o <- rownames(table.AICARInsVSIns)
Tc <- cbind(table.Ins[o,"logFC"], table.AICAR[o,"logFC"], table.AICARIns[o,"logFC"])
rownames(Tc) <- o
colnames(Tc) <- c("Ins", "AICAR", "AICAR+Ins")

4.1 3.1 Gene-centric pathway analysis

# summarise the phosphosite imformation to gene level
Tc.gene <- phosCollapse(Tc, gsub(";.+", "", rownames(Tc)), stat = apply(abs(Tc), 1, max), by = "max")
ids <- gsub("~.", "", rownames(Tc.gene))
rownames(Tc.gene) <- ids

# performe pathway enrichment using over-representation analysis (using the top 10 percent of regulated genes)
geneSet <- names(sort(Tc.gene[,1], decreasing = TRUE))[1:round(nrow(Tc.gene) * 0.1)]
path1 <- pathwayOverrepresent(geneSet, annotation=Pathways.reactome, universe = rownames(Tc.gene), alter = "greater")

# performe pathway enrichment analysis using Wilcoxon Rank Sum test.
path2 <- pathwayRankBasedEnrichment(Tc.gene[,1], annotation=Pathways.reactome, alter = "greater")

path1.sel <- path1[(as.numeric(path1[,2]) >= 4),]
path2.sel <- path2[(as.numeric(path2[,2]) >= 4),]
path1.sel[1:5,c("pvalue", "# of substrates")]

barplot(sort(lp1, decreasing = TRUE)[1:5], las=2, ylab = "Over-representation (-log10 p)")

barplot(sort(lp2, decreasing = TRUE)[1:5], las=2, ylab = "Rank-based gene set test (-log10 p)")

4.2 3.2 Comparison two ways fo 1D pathway enrichment analysis

library(calibrate)
## Loading required package: MASS
o <- intersect(names(lp1), names(lp2))
plot(lp2[o], lp1[o], ylab="Overrepresentation (-log10 p)", xlab="Rank-based gene set test (-log10 p)", 
     main="Comparison of 1D pathway analyses", xlim=c(0, 6), ylim=c(0, 2))
sel <- names(which(lp2[o] > 3.5 | lp1[o] > 0.81))
points(lp2[sel], lp1[sel], pch=16, col="red")
textxy(lp2[sel], lp1[sel], gsub("_", " ", gsub("REACTOME_", "", sel)))
